content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Create a Service Catalog Request page to let your site users view all their open service requests and their details.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions with the Customer Service Catalog add-on license.
The Service Catalog site requires the Service Catalog User permission set and a Channel Account, Customer Community, Customer Community Login, Customer Community Plus, Customer Community Plus Login, External App, Partner Community, or Partner Community Login license.

To build and configure Service Catalog site pages and components: Permissions and licenses associated with the Aura Service Catalog Site Builder

Setup of the Service Catalog Request page is optional. The Service Catalog Request page requires the use of standard Record Detail, Record List, and Record Banner components from Experience Cloud that you configure to link to the Service Catalog Request object.

Create the Service Catalog Request object page.
From the Pages menu, click + New Page.
Select Object Pages.
In the search box, enter Service Catalog Request, and then select Service Catalog Request.
Click Create.

Create the Service Catalog Request object page variation.
From the Pages menu, click .
The Pages dropdown opens and shows the page properties panel for the Service Catalog Request Detail page.
Name the page Service Catalog Request.
Configure the Service Catalog Request object page variation.
Assign a two-column layout, move the column divider to the left, and select Record List with Service Catalog requests.
Add Record Banner and Record Detail components below it.

SEE ALSO

Salesforce Help: Record List
